MINISTRY OF CULTURE AND CREATIVE ECONOMY NEEDS TO REGULARIZE THE RECORDING SEGMENT OF THE INDUSTRY @officialasiwajubat 
@honhannatumusawa 
MOHBAD’s DEATH IS A SIGNAL THAT THE MINISTRY OF CULTURE AND CREATIVE ECONOMY NEEDS TO INNITIATE POLICIES THAT WILL MANDATE REGULARIZATION OF RECORD LABELS ACTIVITIES IN NIGERIA. THIS WILL CURB ILLEGAL ACTIVITIES PROPAGATED BY CRIMINAL ELEMENTS FROM PROLIFERATING THE AFROBEATS CULTURE.

 GOD HAS GIVEN NIGERIAN YOUTHS A GLOBALLY RECOGNIZED CULTURE, WITH UNIMAGINABLE ECONOMICAL AND SOCIAL BENEFITS TO THE COUNTRY AND IT’S CITIZENS, IT IS IMPERATIVE FOR THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT TO ACT WITH PRECISION. 

PARTNERSHIP WITH INDUSTRY STAKEHOLDERS IS KEY TO DEVELOPING THE PROPER FRAMEWORKS THAT WILL PROPEL PROFFESIONALISM IN THE PRACTICE OF THE BUSINESS OF MUSIC IN NIGERIA AND IT WILL INCREASE STATE REVENUE VIA TAXATION. 
Asha Gangali
